FBIS4-60006 "drnes097_j_94003" FBIS-NES-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Saudi Arabia Security Forces Monitor Iran's Hajj Headquarters Security Forces Monitor Iran's Hajj Headquarters Activity at Headquarters Said Controlled LD1805103094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 18 May 94 LD1805103094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Our correspondent in Holy Mecca reported a few moments ago that the esteemed leader's Hajj headquarters is still surrounded by the Saudi police force. We draw your attention to this report: [Unidentified correspondent] Today, the Saudi soldiers deployed special commandoes outside the headquarters gate to prevent headquarters staff and other visitors from entering. Thanks to implementation of this order, staff of the esteemed leader's Hajj headquarters have been compelled to remain inside the building. The Saudi police, after hours of controlling the comings and goings and preventing the arrival and exit of individuals from the headquarters, permitted individuals to come and go for a few hours at 1930 hours local time yesterday evening. Movement in and out of the headquarters was banned again at midday today. Saudi military helicopters also resumed reconnaissance flights and air maneuvers over the headquarters building starting at midday today. The Saudi security officials are videotaping the esteemed leader's headquarters and anybody coming in or going out.
